                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-206-off1081 t18280110-206-victim1243"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JOHN McKENZIE. I am a <rs id="t18280110-206-viclabel1083" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-206-victim1243 t18280110-206-viclabel1083"></join>. On the 9th of January I slept at the <placeName id="t18280110-206-crimeloc1084">St. Andrew public-house, East Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-206-crimeloc1084" type="placeName" value="St. Andrew public-house, East Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-206-crimeloc1084" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-206-off1081 t18280110-206-crimeloc1084"></join>. I went into the tap-room next morning, and saw the prisoner: I had a pot of beer, and asked him to drink - I said I was going to buy a pair of shoes - he said he would go with me - I said I did not want him, but he went; when I got to the shop I changed a sovereign - he was with me - we returned to the public-house; I took off my jacket and waistcoat, and put them on the table - when I came back to my waistcoat, the money was gone from my pocket, and the prisoner had left the house; he was brought back soon after; I asked him for my money; he said, "Here is half-a-crown for you;" I said "That is not all."</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182801100101"></xptr>Prisoner. Q. Were you not beastly drunk? A. I was not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-206-person1244">
                  JOHN 
                  SHIPPY
               <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1244" type="surname" value="SHIPPY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1244" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1244" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a labourer. I was at the public-house, and saw the prisoner and McKenzie come into the tap-room; McKenzie unlocked his box. and took out some things - he went backwards to wash himself - I saw the prisoner draw something off the table, but did not see what; he then went out - I followed him, and brought him back; he then said he had taken half-a-crown off the table; I afterwards saw some silver and halfpence found on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-206-person1245">
                  ROBERT 
                  AIR
               <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1245" type="surname" value="AIR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1245" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1245" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am landlord of the house. There was another man in the tap-room; he went away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-206-person1246">
                  EMANUEL 
                  WHITE
               <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1246" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1246" type="given" value="EMANUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-206-person1246" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took up the prisoner, and found 4s. in a bag, and 6d. in copper, on him; as we went to the office, he said he hoped this job would transport him, as he was tired of this bl - y country.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The prosecutor was throwing his things about on the table; I saw this half-crown on the table, took it up, and said, "Who owns this?" I merely stepped to the door - this man called me back.</p>
               <p>
